    "Together with 11 STEM education innovation centers, teaching methods should be improved (Geng et al. 2019).",
    "In 2016, the \"STEM Education Alliance of Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area\" was founded to increase STEM education awareness (Meng et al. 2022).",
    "This alliance has fostered STEM educational practices in approximately 30 regional schools, tailoring curricula to future local needs.",
    "Despite significant regional efforts in provinces like Zhejiang and Hong Kong, there is a lack of systematic evaluation of how these regional initiatives align with and contribute to China's national STEM education goals, such as those outlined in the '13th Five-Year Plan' and the 'China STEM Education 2029 Innovation Action Plan.'",
    "While regional efforts have made significant strides in STEM educational practices, the disparity in evaluation creates challenges in ensuring that these initiatives are consistently driving the attainment of China's national STEM goals, particularly in less-supported regions."
